meta {
  name: Create SMS Template
  type: http
  seq: 1
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/templates
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

headers {
  content-type: application/json
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{businessAccessToken}}
}

body:json {
  {
    "type": "SMS",
    "name": "Report Ready Alert",
    "triggerEvent": "REPORT_READY",
    "version": "v1.0",
    "isActive": true,
    "body": "Hi {patient_name}, your {test_name} report is ready: {report_link}",
    "header": {
      "enabled": true,
      "type": "Text",
      "text": "Apex Diagnostics",
      "imageFile": "",
      "alignment": "Left"
    },
    "footerBlock": {
      "enabled": true,
      "type": "Text",
      "text": "Reply STOP to opt out",
      "imageFile": "",
      "alignment": "Left"
    },
    "attachment": {
      "enabled": false,
      "type": "Image",
      "files": [],
      "position": "After Body",
      "alignment": "Left",
      "sizeProfile": "Small",
      "shortLinkGenerator": true
    }
  }
}

vars:pre-request {
  businessAccessToken: eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..J55wiEzB-FCqQGSFyaVmqeOfFIFJRrlK5d47mBUpMZ4
}

script:post-response {
  const data = res.getBody() && res.getBody().data;
  if (data && data.id) bru.setEnvVar("templateId", data.id);
}

docs {
  Create a template in the caller's scope. Scope is derived from the JWT
  (`@CurrentProfile`): a **business_admin** token (`active_branch_id: null`)
  creates a **tenant-level** template; a **branch-admin** token creates a
  **branch-level** template for the active branch. `tenantId` / `branchId` /
  `code` are never sent in the body — they come from context (`code` is the
  system-generated `{INITIALS}-Tpl-{n}`). Captures `templateId`.

  ## Fields (all types)

  - `type` (required): `SMS` | `EMAIL` | `WHATSAPP` | `CONSENT_FORM` | `REPORT_TEMPLATE`. Immutable after create.
  - `name` (required): 2–255 chars. Unique per (scope, type) among active rows.
  - `triggerEvent` (required): `REPORT_READY` | `APPOINTMENT_CONFIRMED` | `APPOINTMENT_REMINDER` | `SAMPLE_COLLECTED` | `SAMPLE_RECEIVED` | `CRITICAL_ALERT` | `INVOICE_GENERATED` | `PAYMENT_RECEIVED` | `OTP` | `REGISTRATION` | `PASSWORD_RESET` | `PRE_PROCEDURE` | `AT_REGISTRATION` | `ON_DEMAND` | `RECURRING` | `AT_DISCHARGE` | `CUSTOM`.
  - `version` (optional, default `v1.0`): label matching `vN.N`.
  - `isActive` (optional, default `true`).
  - `body` (required for all types except `REPORT_TEMPLATE`): up to 20000 chars.

  ## Shared optional blocks (any type)

  - `header` / `footerBlock` (HeaderFooter): `{ enabled, type: Text|Image, text?, imageFile?, alignment: Left|Center|Right }`.
  - `attachment` (AttachmentRule): `{ enabled, type: Image|PDF|Both, files: string[], position, alignment: Left|Center|Right, sizeProfile: Small|Medium|Full Width, displayProfile?, shortLinkGenerator? }`. `position`: `Before Body` | `Inline` | `After Body` | `Before Params` | `After Params` | `End of Report` | `Media Header` | `Media Footer`. `displayProfile` (report only): `Full Width` | `Grid 2 per Row` | `Grid 3 per Row` | `Original Size`. `shortLinkGenerator` is the SMS short-link toggle (SMS has no real attachments).

  File fields (`imageFile`, attachment `files`, consent docs) hold filename/key strings only — there is no upload pipeline yet.
}
